Excellent I was at this run in Boston.  Honestly I do not really recall it, but it was the day before my birthday so .... well you know.  Any way great set list, great playing, great recording.  Happy Anniversary to the show!

Listen to the music play.

September 22nd: My Birthday Show One of the very few if not the only time the Dead played on the autumnal equinox, Zodiac cusp of Virgo/Libra, and my birthday - the great day of September 22nd. Plus it was in Boston - 33 miles from a suburb of Kerouac's Lowell where I had my Third Eye opened very wide which led me to move out west to Tucson & Sedona, AZ, Idyllwild, CA and Durango, Colorado. Unfortunately, I was in Durango in 1991 and missed this show... Regardless, it is a great show and love the ability to access this music and listen as often as I want here at The Internet Archive. A fantastic site.
Beautiful Jerry and fantastic keyboards! thanks so much for this - "Stella Blue" alone is pure bliss - the entire concert is simply lovely -and so are the people who brought us this gem!
